We adopted intersection over union (IoU), a well-known evaluation metric, to extract regions in the image processing field. IoU is defined as9\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} \text {IoU} = \frac{\text {Area of intersection}}{\text {Area of union}}, \end{aligned}$$\end{document}IoU=Area of intersectionArea of union,where the numerator (denominator) denotes the area belonging to the ground truth and (or) extracted result. Thus, IoU is equivalent to the Jaccard coefficient. A high IoU indicates that lipid droplet regions are successfully extracted.

